definition: to be underwhelmed/to be less than impressed
abbr. for Uighur 維吾爾|维吾尔[Wei2 wu2 er3]/surname Wei
to preserve/to maintain/to hold together/dimension/vitamin (abbr. for 維生素|维生素[wei2 sheng1 su4])

sentences.english: School teachers probably cringe at this kind of pronunciation.
sentences.chinese: 學校的老師們對這樣的發音恐怕是不敢恭維。

sentences.english: To her aesthetic vision, we can boast about.
sentences.chinese: 對於她的審美眼光，我們可不敢恭維。

sentences.english: I can't compliment him on his English.
sentences.chinese: 他那幾句英語，我實在不敢恭維。

sentences.english: So, too is efficiency in government.
sentences.chinese: 政府部門的效率同樣讓人不敢恭維。

sentences.english: I don't want to be uncharitable, but she's not a terribly good cook .
sentences.chinese: 我並不想苛求別人，但她烹調的手藝也實在不敢恭維。
